		<bioghist encodinganalog="545">
			<head>Biographical Sketch</head>
			<p>Mary Blount Christian was born on February 20, 1933 in Houston. She received a
				Bachelor of Science degree from the University of Houston in 1954 and worked at the
				Houston Post as a reporter and a columnist from 1953 to 1957. From 1959, Christian
				taught writing to children and adults at Houston Community College, Rice University,
				and the Institute of Children's Literature. She created and moderated "Children's
				Bookshelf" on PBS-TV and is a member of the Society of Children's Book Writers, the
				Mystery Writers of America, the Authors Guild, and the Authors League of America.
				Christian is married to George L. Christian, Jr., a book review editor, and the
				couple has three children.</p>
		</bioghist>
		<scopecontent encodinganalog="520$b">
			<head>Scope and Contents Note</head>
			<p>The Mary Blount Christian Papers include background information, correspondence,
				research material, writings, corrected copies, proofs, mockups, presentation copies,
				drafts, and illustrations from the career of children's book author Mary Blount
				Christian. Titles represented in the archive include Hats Are for Watering Horses,
				J.J. Leggett, Secret Agent, The Sand Lot, and Scarabee, the Witch's Cat.</p>
		</scopecontent>
